To change your password on NewsBreak, you need to log in to your account first. Once logged in, go to the 'Me' page and select 'Account Settings.' From there, you can update your password. If you have trouble logging in or need further assistance, feel free to reach out!
Not able to find me page

If you're having trouble finding the 'Me' page, make sure you're using the NewsBreak app. Once in the app, look for a profile icon or a section labeled 'Me' at the bottom of the screen. If you still can't find it, try updating your app to the latest version or reinstalling it.

If you're using the NewsBreak website, the 'Me' page might not be available as it is primarily designed for the app. You can try accessing your account settings directly from the website's main menu or contact support for further assistance.

On the web version of NewsBreak, you might not see a 'Me' page like in the app. Instead, look for options related to your account or profile settings, usually found in the top right corner of the page. If you need to change your password or access account settings, these options should be available there.
